On Sat, 9 Dec 2000, James A. Donald wrote:

> A state is a monopoly of legitimate force.

That's redundent.

> What makes a state a state is  that the policeman can whack me, and I cannot
> whack the policeman.

No, it's that the other people in the society won't accept your whacking
the nice oinkdroid [1]. Why? Because they figure if you'll whack the
oinkdroid what will stop you from whacking them? Nothing.

