[1] There are differences of opinion on the degree of this boundary. In
    some states it is as James describes, you don't strike the officer
    period. On others, such as the US, it is possible to strike the
    officer justifiable if they are themselves acting illegally and
    putting your life in danger. Being a police officer is not absolute
    defence against self-defence.

